<paragraph id="4107B16B06721A0C8413BE692446A6ED" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Alpine brook saxifrage</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9D20C0D7DEA2C0EFB9C39FB5D805A852" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7DBD9D7EF37CED2795B6B7309571698E" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD08F1B3D526E011DBD8E5200A1AF8DE" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Arctic amphi-Beringia-North America</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1634C9A0BF9EABC51CFC01E7FA11F947" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" type="comments">
<paragraph id="924C2B595AC86C3D24C75E5433CB4C59" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3472B9BD09B9D9D27041FE9B8259D8E6" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">
This collection (det. R. Elven and L.J. Gillespie) represents the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="9F54E076A9ABA9896E020D709C35B60E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga rivularis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rivularis">
<emphasis id="7A02C2B3DFF23198969C2F1E1ED75AE9" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Saxifraga rivularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. as currently circumscribed from the western CAA and the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="46344044FF22CEC383B3921998DD67DD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga rivularis subsp. arctolitoralis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rivularis" subSpecies="arctolitoralis">Saxifraga rivularis subsp. arctolitoralis</taxonomicName>
from the CAA. 
<bibRefCitation id="5AE428B2CFF5C46802A337E28285CCBD" author="Porsild, AE" journalOrPublisher="National Museum of Canada Bulletin" pageId="40" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 209" refId="B74" refString="Porsild, AE, 1957. Illustrated Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago. National Museum of Canada Bulletin 146: 1 - 209" title="Illustrated Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago." volume="146" year="1957">Porsild (1957)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="573D14CE7FC9B482DB9BE6FF9F63DA14" author="Porsild, AE" journalOrPublisher="National Museum of Natural Sciences, National Museums of Canada, Ottawa" pageId="40" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 667" refId="B76" refString="Porsild, AE, Cody, WJ, 1980. Vascular Plants of the Continental Northwest Territories, Canada. National Museum of Natural Sciences, National Museums of Canada, Ottawa: 1 - 667" title="Vascular Plants of the Continental Northwest Territories, Canada" year="1980">Porsild and Cody (1980)</bibRefCitation>
previously treated the species in a broader sense and included plants now treated under 
<taxonomicName id="42B5891B274354F6FFDA777542BA7988" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga hyperborea" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyperborea">
<emphasis id="1D0137E32BF46F1C2ACE73DA7BFB122E" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Saxifraga hyperborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R.Br., a circum-Arctic species (all collections of 
<taxonomicName id="2DA0187143FD946FD99C4764E57E0593" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga rivularis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rivularis">
<emphasis id="462343BCC8D229DC48078E476D480F61" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Saxifraga rivularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. mapped by them from the western Arctic Islands are now considered 
<taxonomicName id="DD5DDF10ADACA3219DBCE34470AA5921" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga hyperborea" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyperborea">
<emphasis id="78951AB75E50EFA57C30E097A366A57A" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Saxifraga hyperborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). As treated by 
<bibRefCitation id="BAB9A88C11E993838FFA03B193187924" author="Aiken, SG" journalOrPublisher="NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa" pageId="35" pageNumber="58" publicationUrl="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" refId="B1" refString="Aiken, SG, Dallwitz, MJ, Consaul, LL, McJannet, CL, Boles, RL, Argus, GW, Gillett, JM, Scott, PJ, Elven, R, LeBlanc, MC, Gillespie, LJ, Brysting, AK, Solstad, H, Harris, JG, 2007. Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]. NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa, http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" title="Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]" url="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" year="2007">Aiken et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="928DD5B8A18C089BB68783E33B0325AB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga rivularis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rivularis">
<emphasis id="813C33A0D9B97E147277C595B33C7BCE" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Saxifraga rivularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the eastern CAA, while 
<taxonomicName id="A84BA522DC00521A12836E7592BB3E7B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga hyperborea" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyperborea">
<emphasis id="A6CC6E75EDC30427791715454D1001A6" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Saxifraga hyperborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread across the CAA; the two species are easily distinguished by the presence of stolons only in 
<taxonomicName id="7F27397E2F308F1252BBA424719BB9EB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga rivularis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rivularis">
<emphasis id="DD8E8858D7A4FAF0BABD271A04FE439F" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Saxifraga rivularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our collection fills in a distribution gap in the widely disjunct amphi-Atlantic-amphi-Beringian distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="18F9B1F4BCA741FA86422963445D010C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga rivularis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rivularis">
<emphasis id="1BAAE6518E748893E63BFC1ED7FC5D12" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">Saxifraga rivularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="639FD273FC88A29B5EDD3D0841406E37" pageId="34" pageNumber="57">
Two subspecies have recently been recognized in 
<taxonomicName id="468756EE351801B07805E7B297EB8839" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxifraga rivularis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rivularis">Saxifraga rivularis</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="2AF121A31275F1D81C4532A43B63A39D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. rivularis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rivularis" subSpecies="rivularis">subsp. rivularis</taxonomicName>
with an amphi-Atlantic distribution (and widespread in the eastern CAA) and 
<taxonomicName id="5A75D9D26108DCDE4457E2BD0C62E506" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. arctolitoralis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rivularis" subSpecies="arctolitoralis">subsp. arctolitoralis</taxonomicName>
with an amphi-Beringian distribution (
<bibRefCitation id="8A9A6935605ACB3C09BF7B2FCF345D70" author="Jorgensen, MH" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" pagination="702 - 729" publicationUrl="10.1600/036364406779695988" refId="B57" refString="Jorgensen, MH, Elven, R, Tribsch, A, Gabrielsen, TM, Stedje, B, Brochmann, C, 2006. Taxonomy and evolutionary relationships in the Saxifraga rivularis complex. Systematic Botany 31: 702 - 729, DOI: 10.1600/036364406779695988" title="Taxonomy and evolutionary relationships in the Saxifraga rivularis complex." url="10.1600/036364406779695988" volume="31" year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="92E4091FD8C66D3312C40F0AD09732C7" originalValue="Jørgensen">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
et al. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FE59E3DA74E0EDCD736776756284777D" author="Flora of North America Editorial Committee" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="132 - 146" refId="B16" refString="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, 2009. Saxifraga Linnaeus. In: Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 8 Magnoliophyta: Paeoniaceae to Ericaceae. Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York: 132 - 146" title="Saxifraga Linnaeus." volumeTitle="Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 8 Magnoliophyta: Paeoniaceae to Ericaceae." year="2009">Brouillet and Elvander 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FC2310A2A87EDD941F663D145F6AFAFC" author="Elven, R" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas" pageId="37" pageNumber="60" publicationUrl="http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" refId="B37" refString="Elven, R, Murray, DF, Razzhivin, VY, Yurtsev, BA, 2011. Annotated checklist of the Panarctic Flora (PAF): Vascular plants, version 1.0., http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" title="Annotated checklist of the Panarctic Flora (PAF): Vascular plants, version 1.0" url="http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" year="2011">Elven et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="59F0A4DEF3F96289325553CD716B10B0" author="Jorgensen, MH" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" pagination="702 - 729" publicationUrl="10.1600/036364406779695988" refId="B57" refString="Jorgensen, MH, Elven, R, Tribsch, A, Gabrielsen, TM, Stedje, B, Brochmann, C, 2006. Taxonomy and evolutionary relationships in the Saxifraga rivularis complex. Systematic Botany 31: 702 - 729, DOI: 10.1600/036364406779695988" title="Taxonomy and evolutionary relationships in the Saxifraga rivularis complex." url="10.1600/036364406779695988" volume="31" year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="55B7E72EE299F5D22A1E85CDFDB38F7A" originalValue="Jørgensen">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
et al. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FDF498BC51D12E4267F07259E51A652A" author="Aiken, SG" journalOrPublisher="NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa" pageId="35" pageNumber="58" publicationUrl="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" refId="B1" refString="Aiken, SG, Dallwitz, MJ, Consaul, LL, McJannet, CL, Boles, RL, Argus, GW, Gillett, JM, Scott, PJ, Elven, R, LeBlanc, MC, Gillespie, LJ, Brysting, AK, Solstad, H, Harris, JG, 2007. Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]. NRC Research Press, National Research Council of Canada, Ottawa, http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" title="Flora of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago: Descriptions, Illustrations, Identification, and Information Retrieval [CD-ROM]" url="http://nature.ca/en/research-collections/research-projects/flora-canadian-arctic-archipelago/" year="2007">Aiken et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="D5F4F9DE6ED616E63AFD43E998953D89" author="Flora of North America Editorial Committee" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="132 - 146" refId="B16" refString="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, 2009. Saxifraga Linnaeus. In: Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 8 Magnoliophyta: Paeoniaceae to Ericaceae. Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York: 132 - 146" title="Saxifraga Linnaeus." volumeTitle="Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 8 Magnoliophyta: Paeoniaceae to Ericaceae." year="2009">Brouillet and Elvander (2009)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="5A7D5A771219B4A9865695AD239FBD16" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. arctolitoralis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rivularis" subSpecies="arctolitoralis">subsp. arctolitoralis</taxonomicName>
as present in Alaska, but not known from Canada. More recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="7811B1062E4C902A29B15B65E6294EE1" author="Westergaard, KB" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Biogeography" pageId="41" pageNumber="64" pagination="1262 - 1276" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1365-2699.2010.02278.x" refId="B98" refString="Westergaard, KB, Jorgensen, MH, Gabrielsen, TM, Alsos, IG, Brochmann, C, 2010. The extreme Beringian/Atlantic disjunction in Saxifraga rivularis (Saxifragaceae) has formed at least twice. Journal of Biogeography 37 (7): 1262 - 1276, DOI: 10.1111/j.1365-2699.2010.02278.x" title="The extreme Beringian / Atlantic disjunction in Saxifraga rivularis (Saxifragaceae) has formed at least twice." url="10.1111/j.1365-2699.2010.02278.x" volume="37" year="2010">Westergaard et al. (2010)</bibRefCitation>
presented molecular evidence for the presence of 
<taxonomicName id="F590E1FB3B9030CFEB1E0658BE9D55A4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. arctolitoralis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rivularis" subSpecies="arctolitoralis">subsp. arctolitoralis</taxonomicName>
on southeastern Baffin Island and Greenland, suggesting long distance dispersal from Beringia in the post-glacial period. 
<bibRefCitation id="0EF88C5480192DEF24B9C94ABB028664" author="Elven, R" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas" pageId="37" pageNumber="60" publicationUrl="http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" refId="B37" refString="Elven, R, Murray, DF, Razzhivin, VY, Yurtsev, BA, 2011. Annotated checklist of the Panarctic Flora (PAF): Vascular plants, version 1.0., http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" title="Annotated checklist of the Panarctic Flora (PAF): Vascular plants, version 1.0" url="http://nhm2.uio.no/paf" year="2011">Elven et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
consider 
<taxonomicName id="E97B100CECD7D3E9DB3F1D8803E78E13" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. arctolitoralis" order="Saxifragales" pageId="34" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rivularis" subSpecies="arctolitoralis">subsp. arctolitoralis</taxonomicName>
as present also in the Yukon and the Mackenzie Delta area of the Northwest Territories and mention that there are also plants from Hudson Bay and northern Quebec and Labrador conforming in both DNA and morphology to the subspecies. The two subspecies may be distinguished by the following key (adapted from 
<bibRefCitation id="E8E3E92FD143C97B4D7D813B9BEE9A4A" author="Jorgensen, MH" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" pagination="702 - 729" publicationUrl="10.1600/036364406779695988" refId="B57" refString="Jorgensen, MH, Elven, R, Tribsch, A, Gabrielsen, TM, Stedje, B, Brochmann, C, 2006. Taxonomy and evolutionary relationships in the Saxifraga rivularis complex. Systematic Botany 31: 702 - 729, DOI: 10.1600/036364406779695988" title="Taxonomy and evolutionary relationships in the Saxifraga rivularis complex." url="10.1600/036364406779695988" volume="31" year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="D1D84F4DD6BC865EC41A04D35D1591AD" originalValue="Jørgensen">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
et al. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="02936C14C330C337DC7A9D447A319203" author="Flora of North America Editorial Committee" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="132 - 146" refId="B16" refString="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, 2009. Saxifraga Linnaeus. In: Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 8 Magnoliophyta: Paeoniaceae to Ericaceae. Oxford University Press, Oxford and New York: 132 - 146" title="Saxifraga Linnaeus." volumeTitle="Flora of North America North of Mexico, Volume 8 Magnoliophyta: Paeoniaceae to Ericaceae." year="2009">Brouillet and Elvander 2009</bibRefCitation>
):
</paragraph>
